  "title": "Fixed Income Sales & Trading",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>This role will report to the Head of Fixed Income Sales & Trading in Singapore and have matrix reporting to Head of Planning Hong Kong with the main responsibilities of: </p><ul><li>A business management role to facilitate requests from the business to develop and grow the Fixed Income Sales & Trading business. This would include projects for new products and/or system as well as authoring internal documentations. </li><li>Oversee a team to facilitate business management roles including client onboardings and period reviews, working in close coordination with internal stakeholders such as Legal and Compliance. </li><li>Work on projects that supports the FIST team in aspects such as planning, documentations (such a procedure manuals), consultation with other departments and implementation. </li><li>Maintain and seek ways to improve desk operational efficiencies by working on enhancements where needed. </li><li>Manage risk and control governance issues or error incidents on the FIST team.</li><li>Support all reporting requirements and conduct monitoring of KPIs of FIST team as well as compliance, regulatory and legal issues</li><li>Where required, the business manager will coordinate with related parties within SMFG across geographies for purposes of meeting business objectives.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Accountancy, Banking, Business or Law, or relevant professional qualification</li><li>Min 8 years of experience in the financial services industry, internal/external audit, compliance</li><li>Familiar with relevant regulatory and statutory requirements.</li><li>Self-directed team player who works well with colleagues at all levels to achieve a high standard of work and who is willing to take personal accountability for delivery</li></ul>",
